## 🚀 Usage

Add this to your `Cargo.toml`:

```toml
[dependencies]
{{ library_name }} = "0.1.0"

# Enable optional features as needed
{{ library_name }} = { version = "0.1.0", features = ["serde", "zero-copy"] }
```

### Basic Usage

```rust
use {{ library_name|replace("-", "_") }}::{
{%- for group in protocol_groups %}
    {{ group.name }},
{%- endfor %}
};

{%- if protocol_groups|length > 0 %}
// Example: Use {{ protocol_groups[0].name }} interfaces
let instruction_data = {{ protocol_groups[0].name }}::instructions::SomeIxData::new(
    // instruction parameters...
);

let account_keys = {{ protocol_groups[0].name }}::accounts::SomeKeys {
    // account fields...
};
{%- endif %}
```

### With Serde Support

```rust
// Enable serde feature for JSON serialization
#[cfg(feature = "serde")]
{
    let json_string = instruction_data.to_json()?;
    println!("Instruction JSON: {}", json_string);
}
```

## 🔧 Features

- **`default`**: Basic functionality with borsh serialization
- **`serde`**: Enable JSON serialization/deserialization support
- **`zero-copy`**: Enable zero-copy deserialization with bytemuck (for supported types)

